data.title: Best Seafood Restaurant in San Francisco
data.meta_description: Fog Harbor Fish House is home to the best seafood in San Francisco. Enjoy expertly prepared 100% sustainable seafood dishes with breathtaking views of the Bay!
data.text:
Fog Harbor Fish House: Home to the Best Seafood in San Francisco for Nearly 20 Years

Fog Harbor Fish House is a San Francisco institution that has been serving up the citys freshest sustainable seafood for nearly two decades. The restaurant is one of the best restaurants in San Francisco and is located in one of the citys most popular tourist destinations at Fishermans Wharf. It is known for its stunning views of San Francisco landmarks, like Alcatraz and the iconic Golden Gate Bridge. The dining room is spacious, with large windows that allow diners to take in the breathtaking views of PIER 39 from the restaurant.

Our Commitment to the Community

The restaurant is family-owned and operated by the Simmons family, who are deeply committed to preserving the natural beauty and resources of the San Francisco Bay. In fact, Fog Harbor was the first restaurant on PIER 39 to serve 100% sustainable seafood, a testament to the familys commitment to the environment, and a reason why Fog Harbor is where you can find the best seafood in San Francisco.

Being family-owned and operated, Fog Harbor Fish House has a deep connection to its roots and the city of San Francisco. This family legacy is evident in every aspect of the restaurant, from the commitment to sourcing the best seafood in San Francisco to the warm and welcoming atmosphere. The Simmons family is deeply involved in the day-to-day operations of the restaurant, and they take great pride in ensuring that every guest has an unforgettable dining experience.

So when you dine at Fog Harbor, you can expect a level of care and attention to detail that can only come from a family-run establishment. Its this family touch that sets Fog Harbor apart from other restaurants and makes it a truly unique and special place to enjoy the best seafood San Francisco has to offer.

Experience Extraordinary Service at Fog Harbor

As soon as you step into Fog Harbor Fish House, you will be greeted by the warm and welcoming atmosphere of one of the most popular seafood restaurants in San Francisco. The dcor is simple and elegant and evocative of the citys storied history as a fishing port. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable, and they are always eager to help you choose the perfect dish to suit your tastes and preferences. Whether you are in the mood for a light snack, amazing cocktails, or the best seafood in San Francisco, there is something for everyone at Fog Harbor.

Fog Harbor Fish House has a reputation as one of the best restaurants in San Francisco because the friendly and welcoming service is just as memorable as the delicious food and stunning views. The restaurants staff is composed of experienced professionals who are dedicated to providing every guest with an exceptional dining experience.

They are knowledgeable about the menu and the restaurants commitment to sustainability, and they are always happy to make recommendations based on your tastes and preferences. Whether youre looking for suggestions on San Franciscos best seafood dishes to try or assistance with the wine list, the staff at Fog Harbor is always available to help. And with their warm and welcoming personalities, theyll make you feel right at home from the moment you step through the door.

Try San Franciscos Iconic Dishes

One of the highlights of dining at Fog Harbor Fish House restaurant on PIER 39 is the complimentary sourdough bread, which is baked in-house every hour. This crusty, chewy bread is the perfect complement to any seafood dish, and it is a staple of seafood restaurants throughout San Franciscos culinary scene. In addition to the bread, the restaurant also offers a variety of appetizers and entrees, all of which are expertly prepared using the freshest seafood and best ingredients in San Francisco.

The menu at Fog Harbor Fish House is constantly evolving, as the kitchen staff is always experimenting with new recipes and techniques. Some of the most popular dishes include clam chowder, which is made with clams and a rich, creamy broth, and the cioppino, which is a hearty, flavorful stew made with a variety of seafood, and has a long history in San Francisco. Other popular items include the whole garlic roasted Dungeness crab, the crab cakes, and the shellfish tower. Among all the seafood restaurants in San Francisco, Fog Harbor continues to be a standout.

In addition to offering the best seafood in San Francisco, Fog Harbor Fish House is also known for having the most extensive wine list of all of the PIER 39 restaurants. It features a wide range of local California wines. Whether you prefer a crisp, refreshing white wine or a rich, full-bodied red, there is something for everyone on the wine list. The knowledgeable staff is always on hand to help you make the perfect wine selection to accompany the best seafood meal in San Francisco.

Discover Fog Harbor Fish House on PIER 39

As one of the best restaurants in San Francisco, Fog Harbor Fish House is one of the most sought-after Fishermans Wharf restaurants because it is open 365 days a year. No matter what day of the year it is, you can always count on Fog Harbor to provide a warm and welcoming atmosphere and serve the freshest, most delicious seafood and meats in the city. Whether youre celebrating a special occasion, hosting a private event, or just looking for a place to enjoy a delicious meal, you can always depend on Fog Harbor to be there for you. With the added convenience of being open every day of the year, you can visit us at the best seafood in San Francisco whenever the craving strikes.

Fog Harbor Fish House is a must-visit for anyone looking for the best restaurant in San Francisco. With its stunning views, delicious food, and welcoming atmosphere, it is no wonder that the restaurant is ranked in the top 5 restaurants in the city according to Yelp. Whether you are a local resident or a tourist, no visit to Fishermans Wharf is complete without a visit to a renowned seafood restaurant in San Francisco. Reserve your table at Fog Harbor for an experience that you will never forget.

Find the Best Seafood in San Francisco at Fishermans Wharf

Looking for the best seafood in San Francisco? Youve come to the right place! We are Fog Harbor Fish House after all. At Fog Harbor we are proud to serve only sustainable seafood. In fact, we were the first of Fishermans Wharf restaurants to serve 100% sustainable seafood back in 2012. We care about our oceans and we want to do our part to serve seafood that we can feel good about to help the ocean thrive, prosper, and continue to grow. We are proud to maintain our high standards of serving the best seafood in San Francisco while also upholding our pledge to serve sustainable seafood.

For those who are trying to choose which seafood restaurants in San Francisco to dine in  here are a few things that set the best restaurants apart from other seafood restaurants in San Francisco.

Fresh Seafood is Always in Season

Being on the coast, there are certain seasons for seafood. San Francisco is famous for having certain types of seafood by season, and the best restaurants in San Francisco, including PIER 39 restaurants, serve only the freshest catch. The most famous is Dungeness crab season which opens in November and lasts until about March depending on how that season is going with whales and certain spawning that can happen in the nearby waters. Another popular local seafood is halibut which comes into season from April through August. There is of course the ever-popular salmon that can be caught and served most often from May through October.

If you are starting to plan your seafood restaurant visits based on season, we fully support your thinking. The best restaurants in San Francisco serve fresh local seafood and change their menus seasonally to reflect the best fish available.

San Franciscos Most Cherished Traditions

Another thing to look for when choosing the best seafood in San Francisco is the variety of dishes and the cooking techniques. For a true San Francisco seafood restaurant experience you will likely want to try famous San Francisco-style seafood like clam chowder in a sourdough bread bowl, Dungeness crab, and seafood cioppino. To taste the best seafood in San Francisco youll also want to order dishes that are simply prepared so you can taste the freshness and the flavor of the seafood itself. For instance, a fresh piece of salmon simply grilled with minimal sauce will allow you to appreciate the best seafood the Bay Area has to offer.

The best seafood in San Francisco can be found at restaurants that receive fresh fish deliveries daily and cut that whole fish into portions before cooking them masterfully and serving them soon thereafter right to your table. Many of these eateries can be found in the PIER 39 restaurants as they are right on the water and know their guests value local fresh seafood. Of the well-known PIER 39 San Francisco restaurants, Fog Harbor Fish House, Pier Market Seafood Restaurant, and Crab House receive and cut fresh fish deliveries daily.

Visit Fog Harbor Fish House on PIER 39

What better way to enjoy the best seafood in San Francisco than to enjoy it while overlooking San Franciscos most iconic landmarks  the Golden Gate Bridge and Alcatraz? To accomplish this enticing activity, we recommend San Franciscos best restaurants at Fishermans Wharf that serve fresh seafood while overlooking the San Francisco Bay. There are many PIER 39 restaurants as well as restaurants near PIER 39 that give you the complete experience. Book a reservation for your next visit to Fishermans Wharf!
